h3. Summary

When adding new users to a Bitbucket Server instance, an LDAP sync issue was encountered:

 

{code}
invalid attribute description
{code}

 

Although the "Test" for the LDAP connection succeeded, the sync would fail.

 

Upon further inspection of the logs it was noted the issue stemmed from a typo in the Group Object Filter - \{\{Unbalanced parenthesis}}

 

It would be useful if this error were displayed in the UI when the "Test" is run.

{panel:title=Atlassian status as of April 2017|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3C78B5|titleBGColor=#3C78B5|bgColor=#E7F4FA}
There are changes planned to expose more mail queue information via JMX. This suggestion is currently open to gauge interest, and rationale, in going beyond that with a user interface.
At this stage, it is unlikely we'd prioritise this without additional customer demand.
{panel}

As a Bitbucket admin, I like to see the mail queue from the admin section so that I can determine if the email notifications are blocked ......

This feature is available on other Atlassian applications like Jira, confluence, bamboo, fisheye/crucible ........

On [https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/server/docs/latest/reference/javascript/] the link to "JavaScript API" goes to https://developer.atlassian.com/%22../js-api.html/%22

 
